    "The abstraction of information (contained in form) and the concept of Free Energy that produces Useful Work perceived as function may bridge the conceptual gap between different disciplines to understand our \"Elephant\" better when we describe its different sides with different words.",
    "Information (stored in some cases in form) allows energy to perform work.",
    "The dynamics of information and its relation to the material world are essential for understanding natural processes.",
    "Infodynamics allows the study of the biosphere and the human knowledge sphere and is relevant in most areas of science.",
    "Although philosophical studies have explored Infodynamics, it is empirical physical science that can make it a useful science."
